modules.description: Opens and reloads URIs in web browsers, supporting HTTP, HTTPS, and file URLs. It handles string-based URIs and provides direct integration with the default system browser. Use it to launch application-specific links or refresh web pages programmatically.

Provides command-line options for configuring browser behavior, including the browser executable, a prefix for URLs, and background execution. Operates with command-line terms and environment variables to customize web navigation. Used to launch or reload web pages with specific settings from the terminal.

Reloads or opens a URI in a web browser, supporting background execution and URI prefix matching. Operates on strings representing URIs and command-line tools for browser invocation. Used to dynamically update browser tabs or open new ones based on specific URL patterns.
